track_notes:
A 6.0 mile hike with 3200 of elevation gain. Parking for several vehicles is available at the trailhead/intersection (35.112, -83.807). The hike starts on Trail 386/Gated FS 340B and starts with a gentle climb for the first couple of miles, the next two miles are pretty steep followed by several miles of ridge hiking over a few more peaks. When you reach the ridgeline at about mile 3.4, take a left on the Fires Creek Rim Trail/Trail 72. Around 5.9 miles take a right on the Chunk Gal Trail/Trail 77 to the summit. There is a nice small opening on the summit. 

*** NOTE *** September 2014 - There are a couple of blow-downs obscuring the Chunky Gal/Rim Trail intersection. Even though I was warned, I walked right past without noticing the side trail. Twice!! There was a blow-down on the Rim Trail and just on the other side of it was a sign for the Rim Trail. Turn right and the trail to Tusquitee Bald is right there.
